history.content: I think it's a bit late to make the change officially, since it's past the add/drop deadline.  However, you may be able to work something out with the GSIs where you can go to another section and have it work out--when I took 110, I had to switch sections, and I ended up just having to clear it with both the GSI in the section I was officially enrolled in and the one I was actually attending.

It's actually for my Math110 class, but I do think there are a lot of ppl taking math class here so I hope it's a valid question for EECS101.

Would it still be able to switch my discussion session now? I'll check with math department tmr but I'm just asking here to see if anyone has the previous experience.

All the sections are pretty vacant.
